178 -AWS LAMBDA GENERAL CONFIGURATION (SHORTEST NOTES):

FUNCTION ----> CONFIGURATION  -----> GENERAL CONF ---> EDIT

MEMORY:
- Range: 128 MB to 10,240 MB (10 GB)
- Increments: 1 MB
- CPU scales linearly with memory

TIMEOUT:
- Max: 900 seconds (15 minutes)
- Default: 3 seconds
- Min: 1 second

EPHEMERAL STORAGE (/tmp):
- Max: 512 MB to 10,240 MB (10 GB)
- Default: 512 MB

CONCURRENCY:
- Reserved: Guaranteed max for function
- Provisioned: Pre-initialized instances (no cold start)
- Burst: 500-3000 per region

DEPLOYMENT PACKAGE:
- ZIP: 50 MB (compressed), 250 MB (uncompressed)
- Container image: 10 GB max

ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES:
- Max: 4 KB total (key + value)

HANDLER NAMING:
- Format: filename.handler_function
- Example: lambda_function.lambda_handler

REQUEST/RESPONSE:
- Synchronous: 6 MB (API Gateway, ALB)
- Asynchronous: 256 KB (S3, SNS, EventBridge)

VPC:
- Attach to private subnets
- Needs NAT gateway for public internet

LAYERS:
- Max 5 layers per function
- 250 MB unzipped per layer

COLD START:
- ZIP: 100-300ms (Node/Python), 400-600ms (Java/.NET)
- Container: 1-2 seconds minimum

PRICING:
- Per 1ms execution
- Free tier: 1 million requests/month, 400,000 GB-seconds
