AWS Tutorial 179 - AWS Lambda - Context Object in Function - AWS in hindi

---- WHAT WE GET (CONTEXT OBJECT ATTRIBUTES):
| Attribute | Description | Example |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| aws_request_id | Unique ID for this invocation | 85b043db-37ee-48e3... |
| log_group_name | CloudWatch log group | /aws/lambda/my-function |
| log_stream_name | CloudWatch log stream | 2024/01/15/[$LATEST]... |
| function_name | Lambda function name | my-function |
| function_version | Version ($LATEST or number) | $LATEST |
| invoked_function_arn | Full ARN of function | arn:aws:lambda:... |
| memory_limit_in_mb | Configured memory | 128 |
| remaining_time_in_millis | Time left before timeout (ms) | 8500 |

---WHY WE NEED IT:
1. TRACKING: Get unique request ID for debugging
2. LOGGING: Know which log stream to search
3. TIMEOUT CONTROL: Check remaining time before exiting
